body_html:
@alquraishi I don't deny that the behavior you're experiencing is unexpected.

The reason I'm suggesting you turn to StackOverflow for help is exactly what @yaroslavvb mentioned - without more information or a means for us to reproduce the issue, it's not clear what the issue is, and whether it is a bug in TensorFlow or not. As a matter of policy, that sort of support is handled on StackOverflow. Note we regularly monitor StackOverflow issues, just like we do for github issues.

If you do discover a more concrete problem, definitely do file an issue here.
